The driver of a Bus Rapid Transit, which was boarded by the murdered 22-year-old fashion designer, Oluwabamise Ayanwole, has been arrested in Ogun State.
According to a confirmed source, the suspect, who vanished after the incident, was apprehended by a Department of State Service (DSS) operative in the Odogbolu area of Ogun state.
Adekunle Ajisebutu, the Lagos State Police Public Relations Officer, told reporters that the police also arrested two people connected to the driver.
According to a police spokesman, preliminary investigation revealed that the victim was possibly pushed down from the bus while it was moving.
This is despite the fact that he stated that the Police Command is working hard to take over the suspect from the DSS.
Oluwabamise’s body was found along the Carter Bridge by Ogogoro Community and has been deposited in the mortuary.
